name: Client service with invalid openApi spec is not added

steps.name: Given SecurityServer login page is open
And Page is prepared to be tested
And User xrd logs in to SecurityServer with password secret
When Rest service dialog is opened and OpenApi spec is set to "https://www.niis.org/nosuchopenapi.yaml" and service code "s4c1"
$("By.xpath: //div[@data-test='service-url-text-field']/By.xpath: .//input") should be(empty: attribute value="" and exact text "")
$("By.xpath: //div[@data-test='service-url-text-field']/By.xpath: .//input") should be(empty: attribute value="" and exact text "")
$("By.xpath: //div[@data-test='service-code-text-field']/By.xpath: .//input") should be(empty: attribute value="" and exact text "")
$("By.xpath: //div[@data-test='service-code-text-field']/By.xpath: .//input") should be(empty: attribute value="" and exact text "")
Then Dialog data is saved and error message "Parsing OpenApi3 description failed" is shown
$("By.xpath: //div[@data-test='contextual-alert']//div[contains(text(), 'Parsing OpenApi3 description failed')]") should be([visible, 15 s.])
$("By.xpath: //div[@data-test='contextual-alert']//div[contains(text(), 'Parsing OpenApi3 description failed')]") should be([visible, 15 s.])
